  "raw_html": "<button type='button' role='link' class='btn btn-link p-0 text-start' id='link_1' aria-label=\" State Bank of India & Others versus Ramadhar Sao pdf\"  class='noToken' href='#' onclick=javascript:open_pdf('1','2025','2025_8_1084_1094','2025INSC1010'); ><font size='4'> <strong>STATE BANK OF INDIA & OTHERS<span class='fst-italic'> versus </span>RAMADHAR SAO </strong>- <span class='escrText'>[2025] 8 S.C.R. 1084</span><span class='ncDisplay'>2025 INSC 1010</span><input type='hidden' id='cnr' value=ESCR010006322025></button></font><br><strong>Coram : RAJESH BINDAL<sup style=\"color: #268e97;font-size: 22px;top: 0;\" class=\"tooltip-sup\" data-tooltip=\"Author\">*</sup>, MANMOHAN</strong><br> Issue for Consideration The respondent was removed from services. The order of punishment was set aside by the Single Bench of the High Court and the respondent was directed to be reinstated with back wages. By the impugned judgment intra-court appeal filed by the Bank was dismissed against the the High Court. Headnotes&dagger; Service Law &ndash; Removal from Service &ndash; Respondent joined the Bank as a messenger &ndash; Complaints were received against the respondent for taking bribe for coordination in sanction of loans &ndash; Inquiry Officer submitted his report by holding the<br><strong class='caseDetailsTD' ><span style='color:#212F3D' > Decision Date :</span><font color='green'> 20-08-2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Case No :</span><font color='green'> CIVIL APPEAL No. 10680/2025</font><span style='color:#212F3D' > | Disposal Nature :</span><font color='green'> Appeal(s) allowed</font>   <span style='color:#212F3D' > |  Bench :</span><font color='green'> 2 Judges</font></strong><div class='row my-1 mt-2 border bg-light'><div class='col-auto'><a href='#' class='btn btn-outline-secondary btn-sm my-1' onclick=open_splitview('1','2025','2025_8_1084_1094','2025INSC1010','S')><i <i class='fas fa-columns me-2'></i>Split view</a></div><div class='col-aut